Northeast Passage is a privately funded program of the University of New Hampshire and is a non-profit 501(c)(3) under UNH and the UNH Foundation.  The mission of Northeast Passage is to create an environment where individuals with disabilities can enjoy recreation with the same freedom of choice, quality of life, and independence as their non-disabled peers.  They do this by developing, delivering, and evaluating innovative barrier-free recreation and health promotion programs. Our guiding principles are promoting client independence through education and problem solving, creating opportunities, and collaborating with others to create a strong network of accessible recreation. What sets us apart though, is our auction style bidding system which ensures that properties are rented out at the best possible prices for everyone. We minimize the burden on both parties by offering a suite of built in features:  1) Affordable property damage protection for hosts allowing traditional security deposits to be a thing of the past.  2) A full money-back rental guarantee for travelers.  3) A payment processing system that ensures travelers get what they expect before the host receives payment.  4) Free credit card processing for hosts.  5) Electronic creation, signing, and storage of vacation rental lease contracts.  6) A comprehensive Trust & Safety Center offering tips to hosts and travelers.  7) Reviews and feedback of properties, hosts, and renters.  Whether you are looking to rent out a sunny beachfront bungalow in Florida or find a romantic ski cabin in the Swiss Alps, we have the tools you need.

By providing open and honest communication with our clients, we can empower them and their cases against the teams of adjusters, investigators and lawyers that the insurance companies assemble to minimize client recovery and maximize their profits. By focusing our efforts to just a few practice areas (business law, workers compensation and personal injury cases), we can concentrate on realizing this vision.
